    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "1. Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "I2c master initiates communication to read and write data from/to connected slaves on the I2C bus."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The PMIC(power management IC) driver uses the I2C driver to get data from slaves connected on the I2C bus."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "I2C driver is also used by some applications to get ultrasonic sensors data."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "I2C is a 2-wire bus that can be routed to multiple devices; each line of each bus is supplemented by a 2.2kΩ pull-up resistor.",
        "Each QUP core can be configured to support one I2C interface, always using lane 1 and lane 0"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "1.1. Schematic Diagram"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "SAIL_PMIC connect to SA8775P on SIP board, Bosch hardware team only lead out two test points."
    },
